The paper proposes a novel imitation learning method that focuses on state alignment rather than action imitation. This method is based on reinforcement learning and involves both local and global perspectives. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also includes experiments on image-based imitation learning, which suggests a possible connection to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper deals with dynamics models, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
